Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Stockport","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Stopford  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Stopford","meanings":["English: locative name from Stockport (Cheshire), which is recorded as  <i>Stokeport</i> in 1188,  <i>Stockford</i> in 1283–8,  <i>Stopford</i> in 1347,  <i>Stoppord</i> in 1337, and  <i>Stapporte</i> in 1583."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Stockport was born about 1170, in Stockport, Cheshire, England, his father, Robert fitzWaltheof, was 17 and his mother, Margaret FitzRobert, was 31. He married Maud FitzRichard in 1194, in Stockport, Cheshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1206, in his hometown, at the age of 37."},"et":{"about 1170–1206":"umbes 1170–1206","1170–1206":"1170–1206","1175–1206":"1175–1206","1192–1237":"1192–1237","1199–1249":"1199–1249","1155–1190":"1155–1190","1140–1210":"1140–1210","1190":"1190","about 1170":"umbes 1170","after 1190":"pärast 1190","1175":"1175","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","1192":"1192","1170":"1170","1206":"1206","1249":"1249","1237":"1237","1199":"1199","1210":"1210","1155":"1155","Bef 1192":"enne 1192","Stockport, Cheshire, England":"Stockport, Cheshire, England","Stockport, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Stockport, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1170–1206":"noin 1170–1206","1170–1206":"1170–1206","1175–1206":"1175–1206","1192–1237":"1192–1237","1199–1249":"1199–1249","1155–1190":"1155–1190","1140–1210":"1140–1210","1190":"1190","about 1170":"noin 1170","after 1190":"1190 jälkeen","1175":"1175","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","1192":"1192","1170":"1170","1206":"1206","1249":"1249","1237":"1237","1199":"1199","1210":"1210","1155":"1155","Bef 1192":"ennen vuotta 1192","Stockport, Cheshire, England":"Stockport, Cheshire, England","Stockport, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Stockport, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1170–1206":"environ 1170–1206","1170–1206":"1170–1206","1175–1206":"1175–1206","1192–1237":"1192–1237","1199–1249":"1199–1249","1155–1190":"1155–1190","1140–1210":"1140–1210","1190":"1190","about 1170":"environ 1170","after 1190":"après 1190","1175":"1175","1140":"1140","1194":"1194","1192":"1192","1170":"1170","1206":"1206","1249":"1249","1237":"1237","1199":"1199","1210":"1210","1155":"1155","Bef 1192":"avant 1192","Stockport, Cheshire, England":"Stockport, Cheshire, Angleterre","Stockport, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Stoc